function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> startswith(w, uppercasefirst(w)), words)
end
```
This function uses the `filter` built-in to iterate over each word in the list and keep only those that start with a capital letter. The `startswith` function is used with `uppercasefirst(w)` to ensure that we are case-insensitive, and `uppercasefirst` is used to account for the first character of each word.
